cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of segmenting infant brain tissues from MRI images using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel architecture for the network, which suggests the possibility of it being in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The use of ensembles and suggestive annotations also suggests the possibility of it being in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also deals with the optimization of the network, which suggests the possibility of it being in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper deals with medical image segmentation, which suggests the possibility of it being in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
